description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Mental Health Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Memory Assessment &amp; Community Dementia Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 Nurse &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(Based in Coventry)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 hrs per week (1.00 wte)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you interested in working within our developing Dementia/Memory Services in Coventry and Warwickshire Partnership Trust? Then ask yourself …&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you want to contribute to the specialist memory care pathway that offers a high quality assessment and treatment service and is responsive and accessible to those who need it?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a commitment to provide a responsive, flexible and evidence based specialist service to those people who are undergoing an assessment of memory problems or those diagnosed with a dementia being sensitive to their complex needs and presentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If yes, read on&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your role will include&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing post diagnostic support and post diagnostic interventions for those people who have been assessed and diagnosed with a dementia by the service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For those who meet the criteria for prescription of cognitive enhancers your role will include supporting the patient during the titration process to the therapeutic dose once the medication has been initiated.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The largest part of the role will include conducting the annual review for patients prescribed cognitive enhancing medication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You may also be involved in being part of the treatment plan proving interventions to clients (and their carers) who have an existing diagnosis of dementia with complex presentations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To offer cover to our other community Dementia Teams within the Trust within as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alongside this you will be part of a team that&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Signposts the individual and/or their carer/family members to appropriate resources in the community&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educates both client and carer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Offers appropriate post diagnostic support groups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provides 1:1 support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promotes Positive Risk taking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Most importantly involves and empowers both the individual and/or their carer to make decisions about their care and treatment now and for the future&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you need&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be a Registered Mental Health Nurse with a commitment to this client group&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Some experience of working with this client group and a good clinical knowledge of anti-dementia medication eg &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cholinesterase inhibitors&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;and Memantine is desirable (although some training will be provided) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated and dynamic individual who has a commitment to the positive development of this service, whose aim is to support people to live well with dementia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join a supportive and motivated service that are constantly evolving and will offer you good clinical support and supervision and encourage your profession and personal development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please note Trust interviews are currently taking place through Microsoft Teams, this can be downloaded either through the App Store or Google Play for use on your phone/tablet. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Varney - Team Manager, Arden Memory Services, Longford Primary Care Centre&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 024 76 707968&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
